# WaypointCam Privacy Policy

Effective date: March 25, 2026

WaypointCam is developed by Alsatian Consulting.

This Privacy Policy explains what information WaypointCam processes, how that information is used, and your choices.

## Summary

- WaypointCam is designed to process your data primarily on your device.
- WaypointCam does not require an account.
- WaypointCam does not operate a backend service that stores your captured media or waypoint data.
- WaypointCam does not sell personal information.

## Information Processed by the App

WaypointCam may process the following categories of information on your device:

- Photos and videos you capture in the app
- Location data (when permission is granted)
- Camera telemetry shown in overlays (for example heading, pitch, yaw, roll, zoom, timestamp, coordinates)
- Waypoints and map annotations you create/import
- App settings (for example coordinate format, time zone mode, save location preferences)

## Why the App Processes This Information

The app uses this information to provide core functionality:

- Capture photos/videos
- Geotag media and render overlays
- Show and manage waypoints on map/camera views
- Import/export waypoint data (`CSV`, `KML`, `KMZ`)
- Save your preferences and settings

## Data Storage

- Captured media is stored on device storage in locations you choose (default `DCIM/WaypointCam`).
- App settings and waypoint metadata are stored locally on device.
- The app currently sets `allowBackup="false"` to reduce backup exposure of app data.

## Data Sharing and Third Parties

WaypointCam itself does not upload your captured media/waypoints to an Alsatian Consulting server.

The app uses third-party platform/services for functionality:

- Google Play Services Location APIs (device location services)
- OpenStreetMap tiles via osmdroid (map tile retrieval)

Those services may process network requests according to their own privacy terms.

## Permissions

Depending on features you use, the app may request:

- Camera
- Microphone (video with audio)
- Location (fine/coarse)
- Media read access (import/select media as needed)
- Notifications (platform/version dependent)

You can deny or revoke permissions in Android settings, but some features may stop working.

## Retention and Deletion

You control your data on your device.

- You can delete captured photos/videos with your file/gallery tools.
- You can clear waypoints/media markers inside the app.
- You can uninstall the app to remove app-local data.

## Security

WaypointCam uses standard Android platform security controls and release hardening practices, including signed releases and production network security restrictions.

No method of storage or transmission is 100% secure, but reasonable measures are used to reduce risk.

## Children

WaypointCam is not directed to children under 13.

## Changes to This Policy

This policy may be updated over time. Material changes should be reflected by updating the effective date above.

